  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0ddd\u0db1\u0dca \u0d87\u0da7\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dd3 9 \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd2 \u0daf\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db8\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A 9-year-old child died after getting stuck in a cone",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to Monaragala Hospital Police, a nine-year-old boy who was receiving treatment at the Monaragala District General Hospital died early today (05) after getting stuck in a cone while eating cornedi.",
        "The deceased is a student named DM Lakshitha Madhushan (09), a third-year student of Galtammandiya Junior College, Okkampitiya, resident of Moneragala Suduwathuraara.",
        "On the 28th, this child broke a cone from a cone near the house and while he was eating it, a cone got stuck and was later admitted to Monaragala Hospital.",
        "The child who was being treated in the intensive care unit of the hospital has died. Monaragala Police are conducting investigations."
      ],
